EMERGENCY services are at the scene of a motorway crash involving multiple vehicles. Four vehicle motorway smash causes traffic chaos EMERGENCY services are at the scene of a motorway crash involving multiple vehicles.Police were called at 12.15pm today to reports of a smash between two cars, a lorry and a van near on the M8 near Glasgow City Centre.It is believed one car has been turned onto its roof following the crash near Glasgow Royal Infirmary.Four lanes are currently closed on the M8 eastbound between J15, Townhead, and J14, Fruitmarket.Traffic is slow back to Anderston Cross with drivers warned to expect lengthy delays.It is not yet known how many people are involved in the incident or if there have been any injuries. 